<TITLE> Bangladesh 35-3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 24 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh lost three wickets after winning the toss and electing to bat in the second and final Test against India at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium on Sunday. The home side lost Imrul Kayes caught behind off Ishant Sharma at the start of the second over without a run on the board. Though TV replays showed the ball clipped the top of the pad before going through. Zaheer Khan then grabbed the wickets of Tamim Iqbal (0) and Junaid Siddique (8) to leave the hosts wobbling at 35-3. The hosts made one change bringing in Siddique to replace Shahriar Nafees. The tourists, who won the first Test in Chittagong by 113 runs, dropped leg-spinner Amit Mishra. Pragyan Ojha came into the side in his place, with MS Dhoni and Harbhajan Singh also returning after missing the first Test through injury. However, they were missing VVS Laxman and Sreesanth as both returned home inj
